<h3>Notes</h3>

This includes candidates who received cash and/or in-kind
contributions. ("In-kind" contributions are donations of supplies,
merchandise, etc.) Most were cash.<p>

The candidate names are taken from the name of the campaign committee,
which does not always include the person's full name. In one case in Oregon, a
committee was listed in FEC reports as being a candidate's campaign
committee, but no name was given at all.<p>

The candidate's party was not always listed. This does not mean the
candidate is an independant, just that the data is incomplete.<p>

This list includes contributions to candidates in the primaries. Some
of these candidates may have been defeated in primaries and so will not
be on the November ballot.<p>

