<html><title>More Quit</title>
<h1><img src="quit3.gif">More Quit</h1>

<hr>
Return to <a href="people.htm">People and Organizations</a> |
<a href="../index.html">Ohio Right to Life Home</a>
<hr>

The picture above shows three women who used to work in an abortion facility,
along with Emily, daughter of one of the workers at the
<a href="http://web2.airmail.net/orn">Operation Rescue</a>
office next door. (The Barbie jeep she is driving was given to her by one of
these women.)<p>

Through the outreach of Emily, her mother, and other pro-lifers, five employees
of the abortion facility have now quit. (Indeed, the woman on the right in this
picture is
<a href="roe.htm">"Jane Roe"</a>, the person who initiated the
<i>Roe v Wade</i> court case that made abortion legal throughout the United
States.) The abortionist now requires all his employees to sign a statement
that reads, "I will not associate with anyone from Operation Rescue during
working hours. If seen associating with anyone from Operation Rescue after
hours it will be considered immoral."<p>

