<html><title>Teachers Saving Children</title>
<h1>Teachers Saving Children</h1>
<hr>
Return to <a href="people.htm">People and Organizations</a> |
<a href="../index.html">Ohio Right to Life Home</a><br>
<hr>

<img src="tsc.gif" align=left>
Teachers Saving Children Inc. -- National ...
an organization of Pro-Life Educators
and Concerned Citizens

<i>"Fighting for LIFE ... in Education."</i><p>

"It is the height of foolishness for
professional educators' associations to
condone or support a practice (abortion)
which eliminates tbe very people that our
profession is supposed to serve. They must
cease taking controversial political stands,
especially on non-education issues, without a
clear mandate from their members. Now is
the time to get involved in saving the lives of
pre-born students."<p>

Connie Bancroft, Executive Director<p>
<br clear=all>

<h2>PURPOSE OF TSC</h2>

Teachers Saving Children Inc. -- National
is an organization of pro-life teachers and
other concerned citizens committed to
establishing among professional educators'
organizations a respect for all human life from
conception to natural death.

<h2>NEA ABORTION POSITION IS FIRM</h2>

Please consider the following:<p>

1. The NEA Resolution I-13 on Family
Planning was adopted in 1985, amended in
1986 and reaffirmed every year since.<p>

<i>"The National Education Association
supports family planning, including the right
to reproductive freedom.<p>

The Association urges the government to
give high priority to making available all
methods of family planning to women and men
unable to take advantage of private facilities.<p>

The Association further urges the
implementation of community-operated,
school-based family planning clinics that will
provide intensive counseling by trained
personnel."<p></i>

2. The NEA delegates easily passed New
Business Item 1990-65.<p>

<i>"NEA will oppose any legislation which
will erode the status of <u>Roe v. Wade</u> and/or
which impedes access to and choice of
reproductive health care options, by providing
technical assistance to state affiliates."</i><p>

Rationale: <i>"NEA resolution supports
family planning including the right to
reproductive freedom. Erosion of
reproductive rights by states, currently
provided by <u>Roe v. Wade,</u> must be
challenged."</i><p>

<h2>TSC NATIONAL</h2>

There are many pro-life teachers across the
nation. As a result, Teachers Saving Children
-- National was established on October 1,
1994. The governing body consists of a
Board of Trustees made up of 7 voting
members and the Executive Director. A goal of the national organization is to
assist in the development of affiliate state chapters.<p>

<h2>TSC ACTIVITIES</h2>

Activities include alerting NEA members and the public to
the facts, press articles and editorials, letter
writing campaigns, working through proper
channels for change, and more.<p>

An informative bi-monthly newsletter is
sent to all members. TSC board members are
available for speaking engagements and
workshops. Prayer and financial support are
both welcomed and needed.<p>

<h2>MEMBERSHIP</h2>

TSC membership is open to all pro-life,
pro-family educators and concerned citizens.
Membership in a professional educators'
organization is not a requirement to join TSC.<p>

Annual dues are $25.00 (college
students/retired educators $10.00). To join
TSC, simply fill out the membership form and
send it in with your $25.00. The TSC
membership year runs from September 1 -
August 31.<p>

Contributions and Memberships are NOT
tax deductible.<p>

Web note: Neat as it would be to do this as an electronic form, unfortunately
Ohio Right to Life is not affiliated with Teachers Saving Children
(we just think they're a great bunch of people), so sending a membership
form to us, electronically or otherwise, wouldn't do anybody a lot of good. So
if you want to join them, you'll have to print the
<a href="tscform.htm">form</a>
out and do it by hand. Sorry.<p>

<hr>

"Teachers Saving Children has been called
'the conscience of the classroom.' Your
willingness to dedicate yourselves to the pro-life cause gives great hope for
the future of
American education. Parents can have
confidence when their children are taught by
such courageous and principled teachers."<p>

<center>
Gary L. Bauer, President<br>
Family Research Council<p>
</center>

<hr>

Approved as a tax exempt organization
under Section 501(c)(4) of the Internal
Revenue Code. As a 501(c)(4) recognized
organization, any memberships and
contributions received are NOT tax
deductible.<p>

<center>
P.O. Box 125<br>
Damascus, OH 44619-0125<p>

(330)537-2546<p>
</center>

