<html><title>Ohio Education Assocation Pro-Abortion</title>
<body bgcolor=#c0c0ff>
<h1>Ohio Education Association Pro-Abortion</h1>
<hr>
Return to <a href="people.htm">People and Organizations</a> |
<a href="../index.html">Ohio Right to Life Home</a><br>
<hr>

At the OEA annual meeting, delegates voted to retain the following
resolution: "The Association supports family planning, including the
right to reproductive freedom." In February a survey was conducted by
a group of concerned Ohio educators. Dave Kaiser,
a delegate from Fort Recovery, stated: "Despite the fact that the
OEA president wants to maintain the current OEA position and has
discouraged teachers from responding, hundreds of teachers did respond
to our survey, and an overwhelming 82% want the OEA
out of the abortion business."<p>

Mr. Kaiser commented that many teachers and school employees across
the state are very concerned.  They resent their dues being spent on
non-educational issues, especially ones that eliminate future
students.  He noted that the delegates attending the convention
did not represent the views of most teachers.  He asked, "Why
does the OE Aleadership refuse to survey its membership on this issue
while actively discouraging members from responding to our survey?"

<hr>
