<html><title>Overpopulation: Living Space</title>
<h1><img src="house.gif">Overpopulation: Living Space</h1>

<hr>
Return to <a href="overpop.htm">Overpopulation</a> |
<a href="../index.html">Ohio Right to Life Home</a><p>
<hr>
Imagine a family of four living on a one-acre lot. That sounds like a decent
amount of living space. I'm sure you wouldn't consider them to be living in
overcrowded conditions. But by global standards, they are. Their property is
twenty-eight times as crowded as the world average.<p>

The total land area of the earth, not including Antartica, comes to seven acres
per person.<p>

By the way, personally I have a family of seven living on a half-acre. That's
one-fourteenth of an acre per person, or ninety-eight times as crowded as the
world average.<p>

<a href="7acres2.htm">Objection</a><p>

