<html><title>What About Jan's Car?</title>
<h1>What About Jan's Car?</h1>

<hr>
Return to
<a href="tangents.htm">Tangents</a> |
<a href="../index.html">Ohio Right to Life Home</a><p>
<hr>

The media routinely report (at length) on acts of violence by pro-life
extremists. Ok, but why don't they give the same kind of coverage to violence
by pro-abortion extremists? You weren't aware there were violent pro-abortion
extemists? Of course not -- the media don't report on them.<p>

To take an example quite close to home for us here at Ohio Right to Life ...<p>

On the morning of April 27, 1994, Ohio Right to Life's chief lobbyist, Jan
Folger, got into car, started the engine, and turned in her seat to look behind
her as she backed out the driveway. When she turned to look forward again, she
saw a line of flame in her driveway. She jumped out of the car just as it burst
into flames.<p>

Jan escaped unharmed, though the car was completely gutted. Police
investigators ruled out accident or mechanical problems and classified the case
as "arson". The perpetrator was never caught.<p>

<img src="jancar.gif">
<hr>
