(1970 - 3,731,000 Live Births;    190,000 Abortions)
(1974 - 3,160,000 Live Births;    900,000 Abortions)
(1986 - 3,687,000 Live Births;  1,575,000 Abortions)
</pre>

<dt>That is frightening. Is there no other answer?

<dd>Only the obvious one. Canadians are killing one out of six babies
conceived. Americans are killing almost one of three. Some
European countries have even worse statistics.<p>
</dl>

<p align=center>
<b>WHY NOT QUIT KILLING PREBORN BABIES?<br>
IT JUST MIGHT BE WORTH OUR OWN LIVES.</b><p>

